title: For Sale:  Remington 1907-15 8mm Lebel
postcontent:
Comes with the hard to find three round enbloc and a large cedar box of ammunition. The 8mm Lebel is a very powerful round and is readily available at an affordable price from PRIVI and is adequate for all North American big game. This is a very solid firearm with overall condition is very good for a nearly 100 year old war relic.  The bayonet lug and beautiful vernier sights are intact and flawless.

Because the demand for rifles could not be met by their own industry, France contracted with Remington Arms to manufacture the Model 07/15. For unknown reasons the Berthier's magazine capacity was three rounds while German rifles held five rounds, and British 10 rounds. When World War I began the French quickly realized the problems with the Berthier. The Model 1907 was modified by adding a metal extension to the bottom of the rifle so a five round clip could be loaded. Thus the rifle Model 07/15. It became the primary rifle of the French army during World War I.

title: For Sale:  Collectible Sig Sauer 45ACP
postcontent: This unique 45 cal pistol was one of the very first Sig Sauer guns available in the United States. These were German built guns imported by Browning before Sig was licensed and operating in America. This practice occurred in the late seventies into the first years of the 80's. The gun was built under the specifications of the German army contract which specified a bottom magazine release. The theory was the military didn't want their officers dropping clips to the ground and thereby loosing the magazine. The grip has Browning wording on both sides.  One side of the slide says Browning Arms Co Morgan Utah & Montreal P.Q. The other side of the slide has Sig Sauer System Made in W. Germany stamped on the other side. Very unique to have three countries on one piece. I have owned the gun for more than 20 years and have seldom fired it. I would estimate its condition with regards to the finish as 8 on a 10 scale. Mechanically it operates flawlessly. There is no safety rather it has a decock. Fires both single and double action. The gun comes with a fobus paddle holster, three single stack seven round magazines and a magazine pouch. $650 firm. Call or text two 5 six 7 six 2 4 seven 7 five. No paper work required but I request ID and pistol permit at time of sale.
